description:
Cloister Netting Panel - This lovely netting curtain is a reproduction of an early "glass curtain" or what is now referred to as "sheer". It is a medium to tight weave netting panel that resembles the seine cloth or nets of France.

Rod pocket panels are sold at loom state, and will arrive longer than finished size stated here. When you wash them they have a nice soft texture.

Approximate finished sizes after washing followed by the actual size before washing:
46" x 45" (loom length - 54")
46" x 63" (loom length - 68")
46" x 84" (loom length - 92")

Colors available: Flax (limited quantities)

Hand-woven in the USA. .

title: Gauze Striped Curtains-Pair - SALE - 30% off
description:
Gauze Striped Curtain

Discontinued - 30% off remaining stock - Sale prices will appear in your cart

Colors: Linen, Antique White, Tan
Cotton/Acrylic/Poly
Machine Wash: Cold, Dry: Medium

Gauze was not just used for wound dressing, but has been woven in many forms as recorded from the early inventories of the 1600's. Gauze curtaining was often woven plain, striped or flowered. This one has a very subtle stripe and is extremely durable. It has a wonderful soft textured feel after it has been washed to the sizes listed. If used as-is at loom length, it is more see-thru and when washed it provides privacy and moderate light blockage.

Gauze curtains are sold at loom state and must be washed to achieve the sizes listed.
You get two panels each measuring as follows:
24 x 45
24 x 54
24 x 63
24 x 72
24 x 84
seo_keywords: Gauze curtains, primitive style, colonial style, linen color, handwovenmade in USA

title: Tobacco Cloth Curtains
description:
Our tobacco cloth curtains are hand-woven in the USA. All sizes are in stock.


Tobacco cloth is a lightweight, thin loosely woven fabric with cotton in plain weave similar to cheesecloth. Used as shade covering for tobacco plants, crinoline, tea bags, bandages and curtains etc... Tobacco cloth is a very old fabric with a lot of whimsy. Try hanging cloth on a piece of jute instead of a rod. A great primitive look!


Can be used at loom state and dry-cleaned or soak in cold water and air dry for a crinkled more primitive look. For maximum shrinkage wash in warm water and dry in warm dryer. Tab on bottom of panel for left or right tie up.

Three panel length choices plus pin-up valance:
46"x54" Loom state size - Good for 45" window
46"x72" Loom state size - Good for 63" window
46"x93" Loom state size - Good for 84" window
50"x20" Loom state size - Valance - Six tabs across top for pinning up. Two shown in photo over bed

Also available tobacco cloth by the yard -- see separate product in this category.
seo_description: Tobacco cloth curtains have a tab on either side to swag up in your desired direction.  Very primitive look.  Tobacco cloth is a lightweight, thin loosely woven fabric with cotton in plain weave similar to cheesecloth. Used as shade covering for tobacco plants, crinoline, tea bags, bandages and curtains etc... Tobacco cloth is a very old fabric with a lot of whimsy. A great primitive look!
